Introductory statement Mario Draghi to the press conference https://t.co/ypnjpeY6yS
Draghi: We view the participation of the UK to the European Union as mutually beneficial
Draghi: Our policies are the same policies that have been enacted in other parts of the world
Draghi: Real interest rates today are higher than they were 20, 30 years ago
Draghi: Low interest rates are a symptom of low growth. If we want higher rates, we need higher growth and inflation
Draghi: With rare exceptions, monetary policy has been the only policy in the last 4 years to support growth
Draghi: The experience with negative rates has been broadly positive for the ECB
Draghi: In the first full year of negative interest rates profitability of banks has gone up
Draghi: Broad financing conditions have improved since we took measures in March
Draghi: The Governing Council was unanimous in defending the independendence of the ECB
Draghi: We obey the law, not politicians
Draghi: We have a mandate to pursue price stability for the whole of the euro area
Draghi: In order to reap the full benefits from our monetary policy measures, other policy areas must contribute much more decisively
Draghi: Overall, our measures in place since June 2014 have clearly improved borrowing conditions for firms and households
Draghi: Recovery still dampened by balance sheet adjustments, insufficient pace of structural reforms and subdued growth in emerging markets
Draghi: Domestic demand continues to be supported by our monetary policy measures
Draghi: Crucial to ensure that the very low inflation environment does not become entrenched in 2nd-round effects on wage and price setting
Draghi: Looking forward, it is essential to preserve an appropriate degree of monetary accommodation as long as needed
Draghi: Following our comprehensive package of decisions taken in early March, broad financing conditions in the euro area have improved
Draghi: Further information on the implementation aspects of the CSPP will be released after the press conference on the ECB’s website
Draghi: In June we will conduct the first of our new TLTROs and we will start purchases under our corporate sector purchase programme (CSPP)
Draghi: We have started to expand our monthly purchases under the asset purchase programme to €80 billion, from the previous €60 billion
Draghi: We continue to expect rates to remain at present or lower levels for extended period of time; well past horizon of asset purchases
